subject: RE: [junit] question about Assert.assertEquals
msgSnippet: ... I typically use throw new UnsupportedOperationException to remind me to change the algorithm once I need to... ;) Regards, Ilja
messageBody:
> >Lastly, for the original poster, before J.B. reminds me of
> it: be sure
> >you override hashCode as well, or funny things will happen in your
> >maps.
>
> Absolutely! The universal hashCode algorithm is "return 0;".
> If you need the object to be a Map key, then write a better
> hashCode algorithm.

I typically use "throw new UnsupportedOperationException" to remind me
to change the algorithm once I need to... ;)

Regards, Ilja
